  "text": "Isolation of Phosphorylated Peptides-The peptides released from the thylakoid surface were methylated as described by Ficarro et al. (29) . Phosphopeptides were affinity-enriched from the methylated peptides by IMAC with the use of immobilized Fe(III) [CITATION_1] . The IMAC procedure was modified in such a way that Fe(III) ions were bound to 5 l of chelating Sepharose (Amersham Biosciences) in microcolumns prepared in GELoader tips (Eppendorf). The beads were washed twice with 20 l of 0.1% (v/v) acetic acid, charged with 100 l of 0.1 M FeCl 3 , and washed twice with 20 l of 0.1% (v/v) acetic acid to remove unbound iron ions. The mixture of methylated thylakoid peptides (20 l) was loaded onto the column, and nonspecific bound peptides were removed by two washes with 20 l of 0.1% acetic acid in water and 20 l of deionized water. The bound phosphopeptides were eluted by five washes with 10 l of 20 mM Na 2 HPO 4 (pH around 9.0). The five eluted fractions were collected separately, and each of them was desalted using C 18 ZipTip (Millipore).",
